ilure before moving forward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring ToolProvider and ClassLoader Options**\\n\\nI’m considering using the public API `ToolProvider.getSystemJavaCompiler` since it’s supported in JDK but not in JRE. It looks like TCK prerequisites require JDK as well, which complicates things. I’m unsure if I need to update `build.gradle` with `testImplementation`, but I don’t think direct reflection is required. Using `getClass` seems fine, though I wonder if addressing class 143 and leveraging `serializable ACROSS_CLASSLOADERS` might create a different class loader scenario. There's a lot to think about here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gcm0v0j7S9D80j19951BSv6Q|fc_0cf58f977881a6b7016a2ab55d632081969e3a609038e0eab5", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.mockito.Mockito.when;\n", "newText": "import static org.mockito.Mockito.when;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.withSettings;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mockito.mock.SerializableMode;\n"}, {"oldText": "            StandardJavaFileManager fileManager = mock(fileManagerType);\n", "newText": "            StandardJavaFileManager fileManager =\n                    mock(\n                            fileManagerType,\n                            withSettings().serializable(SerializableMode.ACROSS_CLASSLOADERS));\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 410, "output": 1067, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40389, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781183813819, "responseId": "resp_0cf58f977881a6b7016a2ab54685b88196b48e4c17d7ff1888"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult"